@DATABASE "Ninja Commando"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - N - Ninja Commando"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - N
                   ====================================

                              Ninja Commando
                              ==============



DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(29076,255)"}          29076,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(51763,0)"}          51763,0


                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         I haven't tested the "Lives = x" POKE, but
                         the "Infinite Lives" is mine, and does work.

                         Rastan
@endnode
